com.samskivert.util
Class Multex

java.lang.Object
  com.samskivert.util.Multex

public class Multex
extends Object

Provides support for delaying an action until some set of conditions have been satisfied. When those conditions are satisfied, the Runnable associated with the multex is executed. This class is not intended for use by multiple threads, and runs the action during the final call to satisfied(int).

When the final condition has been satisfied(int), the action is fired and the multex is reset.

Method Detail

satisfied

public void satisfied(int condition)
Indicates that the specified condition has been satisfied. If this condition is the last remaining condition, the multex will be reset and the action will be fired (in that order) before this method call returns.

reset

public void reset()
Resets this multex, setting all conditions to unsatisfied.
